  OTS Logger Plugin

INTRODUCTION

  This plugin enables HTTP logging functionality for OTS components.
  
INSTALLATION

  These instructions are for Ubuntu, but similar steps are required for
  other distributions too.
  
  1. Install django

    sudo apt-get install python-django libapache2-mod-wsgi

  2. Download the latest django xml-rpc plugin

    https://launchpad.net/django-xmlrpc

  3. Install django plugin

    tar xzf django_xmlrpc-0.1.tar.gz
    sudo mv django_xmlrpc /usr/local/lib/python2.6/dist-packages/

  4. Create directory for database and set permissions

    sudo mkdir /opt/ots/
    sudo chown www-data:www-data /opt/ots/

  5. Install plugin
  
    sudo python setup.py install
  
  6. Create database

    cd ots/plugin.logger/django_ots/
    sudo python manage.py syncdb
    sudo chown www-data:www-data /opt/ots/*

  7. Configure apache default configuration

    sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default

      <VirtualHost *:80>
              AliasMatch /([^/]*\.css) /var/www/styles/$1
              Alias /media/ /var/www/media/
              <Directory /usr/local/wsgi/static>
                      Order deny,allow
                      Allow from all
              </Directory>
              WSGIScriptAlias / /var/www/ots.wsgi
              <Directory /usr/local/wsgi/scripts>
                      Order allow,deny
                      Allow from all
              </Directory>
      </VirtualHost>

  8. Copy www files to /var/www/

    sudo cp -r ots/plugin.logger/django_logger/templates/* /var/www/
  
  9. Restart apache

    sudo service apache2 restart

  10. Browse http://localhost/logger/view/ 